l court Saturday asking 6300000 damages from the Brotherhood of Railroad Trainmen and 30 officers and mem bers The action followed arrests in vari out cities as violence continued in a strike of bus drivers affiliated with the B R T The strike was called Thursday to enforce demands for a closed shop and wage increases At Syracuse N Y two buses were stoned and police were hard pressed to handle a crowd they estimated at 300 pjrsons that attempted to halt bus movements Eleven men were held by Washing ton police after a bus driver was forced to a curb and beaten Two Cleveland strikers were arraigned on disorderly conduct charges Damaging and destroying tires windows brakes and various part of motor buses and other equipment threatening and intimidating em ployes and intimidating prospective passengers were cited as alleged of fenses The companies charged the strike was called to restrict limit and cripple the motor bus operations with a view to restoring the patronage of the motor bus operators to the rail roads and increasing the"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-25T19:28:40.852Z", "group": ["ndnp/ndhi", "state-histrorical-society-of-north-dakota-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85042243/1937-11-27/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ndhi:batch_ndhi_jemhadar_ver01:data:sn85042243:00383346162:1937112701:0782/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=423&w=322", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ndhi:batch_ndhi_jemhadar_ver01:data:sn85042243:00383346162:1937112701:0782/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=846&w=645", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ndhi/batch_ndhi_jemhadar_ver01/data/sn85042243/00383346162/1937112701/0782.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 30, "language": ["english"], "location": ["morton", "bismarck", "mandan", "united states", "north dakota", "burleigh"], "location_city": ["bismarck", "mandan"], "locati