 of Crisis EDITORS INTRODUCTORY NOTE When by executive order of May t 1935 the President launched the vast Works Program with the present WPA as its key agency not less than 40 Federal agencies participated in it These with their alphabetical names lending the New Deal a distinguishing characteristic had been hastily organized to combat the emergency in 1933 The Administrations first move had been the Presidents mes sage to Congress on March 21 1933 calling for three attacks upon the problemthe Civilian Conservation Corps for idle young men the Public Works Administration for largescale projects to put lookers into jobs and the Federal Emergency Relief Administration for aiding state and local authorities in general direct relief n todays article President Roosevelt recounts the beginnings of the FERA and its development thru various stages into the pres ent WPA ARTICLE NUMBER FOUR Printed in The News Saturday March 28 In 1933 direct relief work was immediately necessary ko feed and clothe millions of our destitute and unem ployed citizens whose resources and means of livelihood had completely vanished during the years of depression When I first"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-09-28T04:56:55.839Z", "group": ["ndnp/dlc-2020_now", "library-of-congress-washington-dc-awardee-8"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1938-03-26/ed-1/?sp=19", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_bullock_ver01:data:sn82016181:00516999639:1938032601:0871/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=329&w=222", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_bullock_ver01:data:sn82016181:00516999639:1938032601:0871/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=659&w=445", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_bullock_ver01/data/sn82016181/00516999639/1938032601/0871.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united state