c_1kahlo_ver01%2Fdata%2Fsn83045462%2F00280601652%2F1937120801%2F0556.xml&q=business+revival&relevant_snippet=1"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026749/1938-03-01/ed-1/?sp=8"], "batch": ["dlc_hawthorne_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/district of columbia/", "3/united states/district of columbia/washington/"], "contributor": ["library of congress, washington, dc"], "date": "1938-03-01", "dates": ["1938-03-01"], "description": ["8 BIG THREE JOIN TO BREAK JAM IN USED AUTOS Ford Knudsen Keller Act to End Depression DETROIT March 1 1N5 Edsel Ford William S Knudsen and K T Keller today threw the weight of the motor industrys Big Three behind the 1250000 advertising campaign to end the business recession by breaking the jam of used cars in the stocks of dealers In simultaneous statements the first ever issued jointly by leaders of the Ford Motor Com pany General Motors Corporation and Chrysler Corporationthe three men pledged support of their organizations to the drive and ex pressed the belief that a revival of automobile production through a stimulated market would bring a general business revival to the nation INDUSTRY PRAISED i Ford spoke of the industrv as a whole saying The one great contribution the automobile industry made to the nation in its efforts to throw off the last depression was its demonstration of courage in 1 the face of adversity That same fearlessness is evident to I day as a united industry moves forward to start the wheels rolling again 1 Knudsen head of the gigantic 1 General Motors Corporation i stressed the added highway safety i that will"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-07T20:32:10.294Z", "group": ["ndnp/dlc-2020_now", "library-of-congress-washington-dc-awardee-8"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026749/1938-03-01/ed-1/?sp=8", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_