while Sen William H King ID Utah i announced he would intro duce legislation this afternoon for drastic revision of the undistributed prots tax and the capital gains tax The Administration successful in"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-09-28T04:52:14.430Z", "group": ["ndnp/dlc-2020_now", "library-of-congress-washington-dc-awardee-8"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1937-12-06/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_bullock_ver01:data:sn82016181:00516999615:1937120601:1163/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=329&w=225", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_bullock_ver01:data:sn82016181:00516999615:1937120601:1163/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=658&w=450", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_bullock_ver01/data/sn82016181/00516999615/1937120601/1163.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "washington", "washington d.c.", "district of columbia"], "location_city": ["washington"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_state": ["district of columbia"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["5", "0", "sn82016181", "1", "0000000002", "9", "6"], "number_edition": ["1"], "number_lccn": ["sn82016181"], "number_page": ["0000000002"], "number_reel": ["0", "0", "5", "1", "6", "9", "9", "9", "6", "1", "5"], "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "page_id": "sn82016181-1937-12-06-ed-1-1163", "partof": ["chronicling america", "the washington daily news (washington, d.c.) 1921-1972", "serial and government publications division"], "partof_collection": ["chronicling america"], "partof_division": ["serial and government publications division"], "partof_title": ["the washington daily news (washington, d.c.) 1921-1972"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "resources": [{"files": 1, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1937-12-06/ed-1/?sp=2"}], "segmentof": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1937-12-06/ed-1/"], "shelf_id": "02", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "subject": ["washington (d.c.)", "district of columbia", "united states", "washington", "newspapers"], "timestamp": "2026-03-17T15:54:18.389Z", "title": "Image 2 of The Washington daily news (Washington, D.C.), December 6, 1937", "type": ["segment"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1937-12-06/ed-1/?sp=2&q=business+revival", "word_coordinates_url": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?format=alto_xml&segment=%2Fservice%2Fndnp%2Fdlc%2Fbatch_dlc_bullock_ver01%2Fdata%2Fsn82016181%2F00516999615%2F1937120601%2F1163.xml&q=business+revival&relevant_snippet=1"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1937-11-27/ed-1/?sp=17"], "batch": ["dlc_bullock_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/district of columbia/", "3/united states/district of columbia/washington/"], "contributor": ["library of congress, washington, dc"], "date": "1937-11-27", "dates": ["1937-11-27"], "description": ["Berlins Bid for Trade Pact With U S Gets Cool Reception By RAYMOND CLAPPER Germany has been checking around in Washington trying to find some way of getting in under the Hull reciprocal trade program But the reception was cool and there was no sale Germany has been advised that it is hopeless to consider negotiations without first making major alterations in fascist trade practices Manyprobably mostof our officials are not in sympathy as individuals with the Hitler regime ag 4 While they would not allow the official ateesn record to say so some of them feel so wain strongly about this that they would rather OF h not see a reciprocal trade agreement ne g aas gotiated with Germany at this time 99 8 Unquestionably a German American 8 s Clapper trade agreement now would be used for political purposes both abroad and at home and altho little is said about these broader considerations they undoubtedly I have a strong influence here The Hitler I regime is extremely unpopular in Con gress and a trade agreement with Ger many would be used as a vehicle for at tack on the whole reciprocal program Abroad such an agreement might be"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-09-28T04:52:14.430Z", "group": ["ndnp/dlc-2020_now", "library-of-congress-washington-dc-awardee-8"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1937-11-27/ed-1/?sp=17", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_bullock_ver01:data:sn82016181:00516999615:1937112701:0901/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=329&w=226", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_bullock_ver01:data:sn82016181:00516999615:1937112701:0901/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=659&w=452", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_bullock_ver01/data/sn82016181/00516999615/1937112701/0901.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "washington", "washington d.c.", "district of columbia"], "location_city": ["washington"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_state": ["district of columbia"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["5", "0", "0000000017", "sn82016181", "1", "9", "6"], "number_edition": ["1"], "number_lccn": ["sn82016181"], "number_page": ["0000000017"], "number_reel": ["0", "0", "5", "1", "6", "9", "9", "9", "6", "1", "5"], "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "page_id": "sn82016181-1937-11-27-ed-1-0901", "partof": ["chronicling america", "the washington daily news (washington, d.c.) 1921-1972", "serial and government publications division"], "partof_collection": ["chronicling america"], "partof_division": ["serial and government publications division"], "partof_title": ["the washington daily news (washington, d.c.) 1921-1972"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "resources": [{"files": 1, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1937-11-27/ed-1/?sp=17"}], "segmentof": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1937-11-27/ed-1/"], "shelf_id": "17", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "subject": ["washington (d.c.)", "district of columbia", "united states", "washington", "newspapers"], "timestamp": "2026-03-17T15:53:54.997Z", "title": "Image 17 of The Washington daily news (Washington, D.C.), November 27, 1937", "type": ["segment"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82016181/1937-11-27/ed-1/?sp=17&q=business+revival", "word_coordinates_url": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?format=alto_xml&segment=%2Fservice%2Fndnp%2Fdlc%2Fbatch_dlc_bullock_ver01%2Fdata%2Fsn82016181%2F00516999615%2F1937112701%2F0901.xml&q=business+revival&relevant_snippet=1"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026749/1938-02-15/ed-1/?sp=9"], "batch": ["dlc_hawthorne_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/district of columbia/", "3/united states/district of columbia/washington/"], "contributor": ["library of congress, washington, dc"], "date": "1938-02-15", "dates": ["1938-02-15"], "description": ["JAPAN PROPOSES ARMS CUTFOR U S NEWS BEHIND THE NEWS By PAXIL MALLON World Copyright 1938 by King Feature Syndicate Inc All Righta Reserved Reproduction in Full or in Part Strictly Prohibited THE notvervsubtle disarmament proposal in the Japa nese note shows the inside and outside of the world situation The Japanese proposed aboli tion of capital ships in words wringing wet with tears because the same earnest sug gestion had unfortunate ly been turn ed down by the United States and Britain at the London di s a r m a m e nt cons erence The real depth of earn estness in the suggestion is evidenced by the compara Paul Mallon tive naval figures which show Capital shipsU S 15 Japan 10 CruisersU S 27 Japan 26 DestroyersU S 35 Japan 67 Submarines U S 22 Japan l In other words Japan eau nestly proposes disarmament for the United States Her plan simply is to establish Japanese superiority by having the U S and Britain abolish expensive large ships in which they are superior Unfortunately as the Japa nese say other secondary na tions are similarly earnest foe the same kind of disarmament for the other fellow The"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-07T20:32:10.294Z", "group": ["ndnp/dlc-2020_now", "library-of-congress-washington-dc-awardee-8"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026749/1938-02-15/ed-1/?sp=9", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_hawthorne_ver01:data:sn84026749:00205698267:1938021501:0203/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=269&w=211", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_hawthorne_ver01:data:sn84026749:00205698267:1938021501:0203/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=539&w=422", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_hawthorne_ver01:data:sn84026749:00205698267:1938021501:0203/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1078&w=844", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_hawthorne_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205698267/1938021501/0203.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "washington", "washington d.c.", "district of columbia"], "location_city": ["washington"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_state": ["district of columbia"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["0000000009", "5", "0