 down by the United States and Britain at the London di s a r m a m e nt cons erence The real depth of earn estness in the suggestion is evidenced by the compara Paul Mallon tive naval figures which show Capital shipsU S 15 Japan 10 CruisersU S 27 Japan 26 DestroyersU S 35 Japan 67 Submarines U S 22 Japan l In other words Japan eau nestly proposes disarmament for the United States Her plan simply is to establish Japanese superiority by having the U S and Britain abolish expensive large ships in which they are superior Unfortunately as the Japa nese say other secondary na tions are similarly earnest foe the same kind of disarmament for the other fellow The"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-07T20:32:10.294Z", "group": ["ndnp/dlc-2020_now", "library-of-congress-washington-dc-awardee-8"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026749/1938-02-15/ed-1/?sp=9", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_hawthorne_ver01:data:sn84026749:00205698267:1938021501:0203/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=269&w=211", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_hawthorne_ver01:data:sn84026749:00205698267:1938021501:0203/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=539&w=422", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_hawthorne_ver01:data:sn84026749:00205698267:1938021501:0203/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1078&w=844", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_hawthorne_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205698267/1938021501/0203.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "washington", "washington d.c.", "district of columbia"], "location_city": ["washington"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_state": ["district of columbia"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number":